<h1>Problem 410 - 2014 France TST P4 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer and \(x_1,x_2,\ldots,x_n\) be positive reals. Show that there are numbers \(a_1,a_2,\ldots, a_n \in \{-1,1\}\) such that the following holds:
\[a_1x_1^2+a_2x_2^2+\cdots+a_nx_n^2 \ge (a_1x_1+a_2x_2 +\cdots+a_nx_n)^2\]</p>
